can utter the horrible perpexity of the <HI>Sodomite<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI>
on that day, under this unthought of, unexpe|cted,
sudden, and so dreadful un-heard-of Judg|ment?
when they opened their windows and
doors of their houses in the morning, and per|ceived
the fashion of the heavens to be altered
and the tempest of Fire and Brimstone to beat <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
upon them so sorely and suddenly; when the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word">
was strangely converted into fire, and such scal|ding
sulphurious matter enkindled by the brea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">
of God did fall upon them; when the whol<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">
place was put into flames together, and ever
house was set on Fire by this Fire from Heaven
when they saw if the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> went forth of doors
<PB N="221" REF="115">
they should be burnt by the fire of Heaven,
if they stayed within, they should be burnt by the
fire of their houses; when there was such a dreadful
burning heat by the Fire, accompanied with such
a stinking, noisome, suffocating smoke by the
